                                    .media-content
                                        h3.title.is-4 How is a decentralized network different from the traditional web?
                                        p Decentralization is a key aspect of PiperNet. Traditionally, to access data on a website, you needed to connect to a single server containing that data. This method of storing data makes it easy for third parties to get access to it, corrupt it or even delete it. In PiperNet it is securely stored on multiple devices in the network, which makes it harder to hack and interfere with your data.

                        .card.block
                            .card-content
                               .media
                                    .media-left
                                        figure.image.is-64x64
                                            img.is-rounded(src="https://bulma.dev/placeholder/pictures/bg_circle.svg?primary=00d1b2", alt="")
                                    .media-content
                                        h3.title.is-4 Why shouldn't I just store my data on a Hooli Box?
                                        p That's just the thing - if you store your data in a single place, like Gavin Belsons' poorly-made server box, your data will very susceptible to hacking. Whereas on PiperNet, your data is safe with many copies to back it up from.

                        .card.block
                            .card-content
                               .media
                                    .media-left
                                        figure.image.is-64x64
                                            img.is-rounded(src="https://bulma.dev/placeholder/pictures/bg_circle.svg?primary=00d1b2", alt="")
                                    .media-content
                                        h3.title.is-4 What makes PiperNet so safe?
                                        p Our proprietary middle-out compression algorithm allows data to flow so fast that it can't be hacked! But, in all seriousness, the algorithm helps but it's the public, immutable ledger that makes it secure. This enables PiperNet users to exchange data without risk of it being intercepted by third parties.

                        .card.block
                            .card-content
                               .media
